posts.cooked: Hi, Our team is trying to run a motor using Spark maxes but it keeps giving this error: [CAN SPARK MAX] IDs: 1, The firmware is too old and needs to be updated. Refer to REVLib Information - SPARK MAX for details. All the spark maxes are update to 1.5.2, but according to the REV website, the latest firmware version is 1.6.3, which we are not able to figure out how to upload. Rev hardware client only allows to either downgrade to 1.5.1 or update to 1.5.2. Could anyone please help us upload the latest firmware on to the SPARK.

Are you on a computer that is connected to the internet? Did you allow the REV Hardware Client to be a trusted application with access to your network? As far as I recall we are always just able to have the hardware client check automatically for updates for our devices.

posts.name: Mert Ata BABER
posts.cooked: Is it a school or work network? Those can block some outbound connections. Also, I think you can try reinstalling RHC.

posts.name: MetabolicCloth
posts.cooked: If you can’t get it to check for updates, the easiest fix would probably to go to REVs site and download the latest version of Hardware Client yourself. Then you can uninstall the old and install the new.

Our team has been having this same issue. Even after redownloading the REV hardware client we weren’t able to check for updates and get the new versions. We even tried following the troubleshooting guide on the REV website and found no success.
When did you buy the SparkMAX’s?

posts.name: dyanoshak
posts.cooked:
If the Hardware Client isn’t finding the latest firmware, it is likely a firewall or proxy issue with a school or work network. Try checking for updates on a different network.

Additionally, we pushed an update to our docs site with SPARK MAX firmware version 1.6.3 a bit too early. At this moment in time, the Hardware Client should be displaying version 1.6.2 for the latest SPARK MAX firmware. Version 1.6.3 will officially release very soon.

Yea it seemed like the school network was the reason we were not able to update, but we are facing another issue now: we are not able to run the neo motor using REV Hardware client or code. The spark max is just blinking pink. Is there any way to fix this?
